clark george a page 1 memorial resolution george a clark 1918 the academic council of the leland stanford junior university wishes to record its sense of loss in the death of george archibald clark mr clark had been connected with the university from the time of its opening coming first as a graduate student in latin he soon began to assist dr jordan as stenographer and was in 1896 appointed secretary to the president in this capacity as university secretary from 1909 to the time of his death mr clark rendered constant and generous service winning the regard and affection of all by his devotion to duty and by his uniform kindness and unselfishness while as secretary to the united states fur seal commission and later as special investigator for the bureau of fisheries he rendered important public service in the death of mr clark the university has lost one of its most loyal and useful members and the faculty a well loved colleague and friend at murray fernando sanford gc price
